PackageManagerProxy * mpProxy

Detailed Description

Class for retrieving various kinds of information related to the application packages that are currently installed on the device. 

 // The following sample shows how to use PackageManager to get the sevice info.

 using gaia::base::Vector;

 MyPage::onInit(Persistence* const savedInstenceState) {
   PackageManager *pm = new PackageManager(*this);

   // Following sample code get all launch pages.

   Demand* d = new Demand("gaia.intent.action.MAIN");
   d->addCategory(Demand::CATEGORY_LAUNCHER());

   base::Vector<ResolveInfo> rInfoVec = pm->queryDemandPages(*d, 0);
   ResolveInfo rInfo;
   for (size_t i = 0; i < rInfoVec.size(); i++) {
       rInfo = rInfoVec[i];

       // need check rInfo.
       if (rInfo.isValid()) {
           rInfo.getPriority();
           rInfo.loadLabel(*pm).string();

           graphics::Drawer* drawer;
           drawer = rInfo.loadIconN(*pm);
           if (drawer != NULL) {
               drawer->getOpacity();
           }
       }
   }

   // Following sample code get one specified page.

   rInfo = pm->resolvePage(*d, 0);
   if (rInfo.isValid()) {
       rInfo.getPriority();
       rInfo.loadLabel(*pm).string();

       graphics::Drawer* drawer;
       drawer = rInfo.loadIconN(*pm);
       if (drawer != NULL) {
           drawer->getOpacity();
       }
   }

   delete(d);

   // Following sample code get all installed Packages.

   base::Vector<PackageInfo> pPkgInfo;
   pPkgInfo = pm->getInstalledPackages(PackageManager::GET_DELEGATES |
              PackageManager::GET_PAGES |
              PackageManager::GET_PERMISSIONS);
   for (size_t i = 0; i < pPkgInfo.size(); i++) {
       PackageInfo pi = pPkgInfo[i];

       if (!pi.isValid()) {
           continue;
       }

       GLOG(LOG_TAG, LOGINFO, "%s", pi.getPackageName().string());

       // get pages.
       base::Vector<PageInfo> pInfoVec;
       pInfoVec = pi.getPages();
       // ...
   }

   // Following sample code check permisson is valid or not.

   String permStr= "gaia.permission.RECEIVE_SMS";
   PackageManager::PERM_CHECK_RESULT ckRet = checkPermission(
           permStr, pPkgInfo[0].getPackageName());
   if (ckRet == PackageManager::PERMISSION_DENIED) {
       GLOG(LOG_TAG, LOGINFO, "Permission %s DENIED!", permStr.string());
   }

   // Get one specified permission.

   PermissionInfo permInfo;
   permInfo =  pm->getPermissionInfo(permStr, 0);
   // for PermissionInfo inherits from PackageItemInfo
   if (permInfo.isValid()) {
       GLOG(LOG_TAG, LOGINFO, "%d", permInfo.getProtectionLevel());
       GLOG(LOG_TAG, LOGINFO, "%s", permInfo.getName().string());
       // ...
   }

   // Get one specified provider.
   ProviderInfo pvdInfo = pm->getProviderInfo("com.example.widgettest",
           ".DataCarousel", 0);
   if (pvdInfo.isValid()) {
       pvdInfo.getReadPermission().string();
       // ...
   }

   delete(pm);

   return;
 }

Definition at line 255 of file PackageManager.h.

enum gaia::core::PackageManager::PACKAGEINFO_FLAG

PackageInfo flag.

Enumerator:
GET_PAGES 

PackageInfo flag: return information about pages in the package in PackageInfo#getPages().

GET_RECEIVERS 

PackageInfo flag: return information about demand receivers in the package in PackageInfo#getReceivers().

GET_DELEGATES 

PackageInfo flag: return information about delegates in the package in PackageInfo#getDelegates().

GET_PROVIDERS 

PackageInfo flag: return information about content providers in the package in PackageInfo#getProviders().

GET_DEMAND_FILTERS 

PackageInfo flag: return information about the demand filters supported by the page.

GET_DISABLED_COMPONENTS 

PackageInfo flag: include disabled components in the returned info.

GET_PERMISSIONS 

PackageInfo flag: return information about permissions in the package in PackageInfo#getPermissions().

GET_UNINSTALLED_PACKAGES 

Flag parameter to retrieve all applications(even uninstalled ones) with data directories.

This state could have resulted if applications have been deleted with flag DONT_DELETE_DATA with a possibility of being replaced or reinstalled in future

enum gaia::core::PackageManager::PERM_CHECK_RESULT

Permission check result.

Enumerator:

Permission check result: this is returned by checkPermission if the permission has been granted to the given package.

int32_t  flags 
) const

Retrieve all of the information we know about a particular package/application.

Parameters:

base::Vector<ApplicationInfo> gaia::core::PackageManager::getInstalledApplications ( int32_t  flags) const

Return a List of all application packages that are installed on the device.

If flag GET_UNINSTALLED_PACKAGES has been set, a list of all applications including those deleted with DONT_DELETE_DATA(partially installed apps with data directory) will be returned.

Parameters:
flagsAdditional option flags. Use any combination of GET_META_DATA, GET_UNINSTALLED_PACKAGES to modify the data returned.
Returns:
A List of ApplicationInfo objects, one for each application that is installed on the device. In the unlikely case of there being no installed applications, an empty list is returned. If flag GET_UNINSTALLED_PACKAGES is set, a list of all applications including those deleted with DONT_DELETE_DATA (partially installed apps with data directory) will be returned.
See also:
GET_META_DATA
GET_UNINSTALLED_PACKAGES
